                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12995937" author="larsgeorge" created="Thu, 17 Feb 2011 17:24:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suggested on IRC that we should add it to the UIs (master/regionserver) but also JMX for example. For the shell it would be more the current shell process and therefore limited. Or we could add a call to all servers through RPC to retrieve the config and print it locally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also need this so it can be exposes through REST and displayed in the HBase Explorer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12995942" author="stack" created="Thu, 17 Feb 2011 17:33:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a good idea.  Lets do it.  Should make it so can change settings too at least when going via jmx. In jmx can expose the type also &amp;#8211; int, long, String, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050024" author="stack" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2011 20:56:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is available when hbase runs on hadoop 0.22 if you browse to the /conf servlet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14066953" author="stack" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2014 22:02:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Implemented a while back.  Browse to /conf&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
